{
  "text": "To analyze these, Figure 6 shows the categories' bursts, according to Kleinberg's burstdetection algorithm [CITATION_1] . [CITATION_2] reinforces that such an algorithm is adapted to identify emergent research-front concepts. To elucidate the use of such algorithms for the above categories, it is worth highlighting that \"the burst-detection algorithm can be adapted for detecting sharp increases of interest in a specialty\" (Chen, 2006, p. 364) . Although [CITATION_3] states that the original algorithm was developed to detect the bursts of single words, \"the algorithm is generic enough to be applied to a time series of multiword terms or citations of articles\" (Chen, 2006, p. 364) .",
